name: NYDailyNews
text:
Upstate New Yorkers received an urgent message on their phones nearly 19 years to the minute terrorists flew two planes into the WTC.

An official for the Buffalo suburb of Tonawanda said the unfortunately timed alert was the result of a “training error."
https://t.co/fr4aKWtUbl

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Several students at Ohio's Miami University hosted a party AFTER testing positive for coronavirus.

“Aren’t you supposed to be quarantining?” an officer asked one of the infected students.
 “Yeah, that’s why I’m at my house," he replied.
https://t.co/fV88GTuFjD
